The Abuja Municipal Area Council (AMAC) has called on all traditional rulers in the area council to sensitise members of their communities on precautionary measures to guard against contacting the deadly coronavirus. Head of Primary Healthcare Centres (PHC) in AMAC, Dr Modupe Adeyinka, who made the call when she led a team on a sensitisation campaign to the Chief of Garki Palace, explained that the essence of the campaign was to ensure that those at the grassroots get the correct information on how to prevent the disease. Adeyinka emphasised the need for social distancing, constant hand washing, with soap and running water, use of hand sanitizers, covering of mouth while coughing or sneezing, among others. Responding, the Chief of Garki, Dr Usman Nga Kupi, commended the area council for bringing the sensitisation campaign to the community. Kupi gave an assurance that he would ensure that his community leaders convey the correct message to the people.